orset/IMG_2642.jpg" alt=""> </a><div class="amazingcarousel-hover-effect" style="display:none;position:absolute;left:0;top:0;width:100%;height:100%;cursor:pointer;background-image:url('https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/hoveroverlay-64-64-6.png');background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:center center;"></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item" style="display: block; position: relative; background-image: none; background-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: left; width: 150px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container" style="position: relative; margin: 0px 2px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/IMG_2644.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/IMG_2644.jpg" alt=""> </a><div class="amazingcarousel-hover-effect" style="display:none;position:absolute;left:0;top:0;width:100%;height:100%;cursor:pointer;background-image:url('https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/hoveroverlay-64-64-6.png');background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:center center;"></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><div style="clear:both;"></div></ul></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-prev" style="overflow: hidden; position: absolute; cursor: pointer; width: 32px; height: 32px; background: url(&quot;https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/arrows-32-32-1.png&quot;) left top no-repeat; display: block;"></div><div class="amazingcarousel-next" style="overflow: hidden; position: absolute; cursor: pointer; width: 32px; height: 32px; background: url(&quot;https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/arrows-32-32-1.png&quot;) right top no-repeat; display: block;"></div></div></div></div></div><p><strong>Features:</strong></p><ul><li>Front busk corset;</li><li>A corset for a teenager body proportions;</li><li>Tiered skirt with ruffles.</li></ul><p><strong>Skills you gain:</strong></p><ul><li>How to sew a teens corset with a steel busk;</li><li>How to customize a standard corset pattern to make it suitable for a teenage girl;</li><li>How to&nbsp;make a perfect skirt with many ruffles;</li><li>Original corset decorations.</li></ul><p><strong>Where to use:</strong></p><ul><li>An exclusive fancy dress for&nbsp;your teenage child;</li><li>Perfect solution for proms, celebrations, costume parties and other special events.</li></ul><p><strong>Author:</strong>&nbsp;Tatiana Kozorovitsky</p><p><strong>Total length:</strong>&nbsp;4h 23m</p></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="transcript"><div class="overlay"></div><div itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"> <span itemprop="publisher" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Organization"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy"> <span itemprop="logo" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="text" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="https://www.facebook.com/corsetacademy"> </span> <span itemprop="author" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tatiana Kozorovitsky"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="width" content="128"><meta itemprop="height" content="128"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/jpeg"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/author/infocorsetacademy-net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="http://www.corsetacademy.net"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-8-adjusting-the-size-of-the-corset-sewing-on-the-rest-of-the-bones/"><meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-8-adjusting-the-size-of-the-corset-sewing-on-the-rest-of-the-bones/"><meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-08-08T20:36:58+00:00"><meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2018-08-08T20:36:58+00:00"><meta itemprop="copyrightYear" content="2018"><meta itemprop="inLanguage" content="en_US"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tutorial 8. Adjusting the Size of the Corset.&nbsp; Sewing On the Rest of the Bones."><meta itemprop="headline" content="Tutorial 8. Adjusting the Size of the Corset.&nbsp; Sewing On the Rest of the Bones."><meta itemprop="description" content="Before I can continue working on the corset, I need to make sure the size of the lining corresponds with Olga's measurements"><meta itemprop="articleSection" content="Corset with a Front Busk for 15 Years Old Girl"><meta itemprop="keywords" content="corset with a front busk for 15 years old girl, video"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><div itemprop="articleBody"><h1>Tutorial 8. Adjusting the Size of the Corset.&nbsp; Sewing On the Rest of the Bones.</h1><p>Before I can continue working on the corset, I need to make sure the size of the lining corresponds with Olga's measurements. You can still adjust it at this stage:&nbsp; re-sew the side seams, rip off some bones, adjust the back princess seams, etc.</p><p><strong>I measure the corset along the waistline. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%208.files/image002.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>There is one extra centimeter. I need to shift the side seams 0.5cm inwards in the waist. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%208.files/image004.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I measure it under the bust </strong>and compare the result with the table. I stretch the corset a little to check whether the measurement was taken correctly. It's all good here.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%208.files/image006.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>Now, the Bust Circumference. </strong>It is fine.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%208.files/image008.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>And the Stomach Circumference: </strong>it is good, too.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%208.files/image010.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>The only place that needs to be adjusted is the waistline. I make corresponding markings.&nbsp; </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%208.files/image012.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>And I re-sew the side seams along the new lines and remove the previous stitching.</strong> That is all. Now I can be sure that the size of the corset corresponds with the girl's measurements.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%208.files/image014.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I press open the side seams.</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%208.files/image016.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%208.files/image018.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>Since the side seam is very curvy, I deepen the notches to prevent the seam allowances from pulling on it. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%208.files/image020.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>Now I can lay a narrow Rigilene bone along the top edge of the corset. </strong>I step 1mm down from the stay-stitching and sew the bone on with two parallel rows of stitches because I won't need to push any vertical bones underneath it.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%208.files/image022.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%208.files/image024.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I sew another narrow Rigilene bone on along the bottom edge of the corset starting form the slit bone and stopping about 1.5cm from the vertical row of stay-stitches</strong>. There will be a steel busk there and we don't need a bone under it. I secure the bone with two parallel rows of stitches.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%208.files/image026.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>And I do the same on the other half of the corset.</strong></p><p><strong>I add a bone along the top edge </strong>going from the middle of the back to the cup. I slightly pull the fabric to me to avoid gathering it under the bone.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%208.files/image028.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I lay a bone at a busk width from the edge and sew it on stopping at the slit bone.&nbsp; </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%208.files/image030.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>I slightly gather a narrow Rigilene bone by pulling out the fishing lines and sew it on along the bottom edge of the corset. </strong>The bottom edge is somewhat rounded so the bone needs to be flexible. I sew it on with two parallel rows of stitches.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%208.files/image032.jpg" alt=""></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%208.files/image034.jpg" alt=""></p><p><strong>And I do the same on the other half of the corset.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/transcritps/Tutorial%208.files/image036.jpg" alt=""></strong></p></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="pattern"><p>Sewing patterns are in PDF format.</p><p>To print sewing patterns open the files, press “print” and choose “<strong>PRINT IN ACTUAL SIZE</strong>“.</p><p>In each&nbsp;file the pattern is divided &nbsp;to A4 paper sheets for home printer.</p> <a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/Front-Busk-Corset/patterns/FrontBuskCorset.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> Front Busk Corset Pattern</a><br></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="diploma"><div class="dark-get-started margin-0"><p>In order to receive the Corset Academy graduation diploma you need to submit your graduation work.<br> Upload the photo of the garment that you made after completing the course.<br> I will personally review your work.<br> After the approval you will receive a personalized diploma to your email box, no longer than within 1 business day.</p><p class="text-right">Tatiana Kozorovitsky.</p><form id="diplomaForm"><h4>Your datails:</h4><div class="form-group"> <input type="text" id="firstname" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter first name" required=""><p class="firstname error">Enter your first name</p></div><div class="form-group"> <input type="text" id="lastname" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter last name" required=""><p class="lastname error">Enter your last name</p></div><h4>Choose a course:</h4><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option1" value="1"> <label for="option1"> <em>Wedding gowns design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option2" value="2"> <label for="option2"> <em>Evening dresses design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option3" value="3"> <label for="option3"> <em>Corsetry design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><p class="course error margin-10-bottom">Select course</p><div class="form-group"> <label class="uploadbutton"><div class="button">Choose file</div><div class="pull-left"><div class="input">No file selected</div></div> <input type="file" id="fileupload" name="files[]" data-url="https://corsetacademy.net/diploma/upload/"> </label><div id="progress" class="progress" style="display: none;"><div class="bar progress-bar progress-bar-warning progress-bar-striped active" role="progressbar" style="width: 0%;"></div></div> <input type="hidden" id="uploadDataUrl"><p class="upload error">Please upload photo of your work.</p><p>Max file size 2 Mb</p></div> <input type="hidden" id="userEmail" value="ngochuy.mmt@gmail.com"> <button id="submitDiploma" type="submit" class="btn btn-green-simple">Submit</button><h3 id="submitSpinner" class="text-center" style="display:none"><i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin"></i></h3></form><h4 id="statusAnswer" class="text-center"></h4><div class="clearfix"></div><h3 class="get-pro text-center">The example of the diploma:</h3> <a href="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/diploma_example.png" class="wplightbox" title="Diploma Example"><div id="diploma_example"></div> </a></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="faq"><p class="text-center"><i class="fa fa-spinner fa-pulse fa-3x"></i></p></div></div></div></div>
 
